  "timeframe": "1m",
  "market_context": "On the 1-minute chart, price swept a previous swing low and produced multiple stacked fair value gaps overhead. Instead of an aggressive reclaim, price stalled and began consolidating near the lows after the sweep.",
  "key_observation": "Although liquidity was taken below the prior low, price failed to close back through the cluster of fair value gaps in a decisive V-shape manner, instead drifting into consolidation — invalidating the inversion fair value gap setup.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the sweep of the previous swing low as the liquidity grab event.",
    "Step 2: Recognize multiple fair value gaps overhead and treat the cluster as one combined FVG zone for the inversion test.",
    "Step 3: Observe that price did not aggressively close through the FVG cluster, so no valid IFVG/V-shape reversal formed.",
    "Step 4: Note that price instead consolidates after the sweep, suggesting any upside is likely just running consolidation highs before continuing lower.",
    "Step 5: Conclude this setup must be avoided due to lack of the aggressive reversal signature."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "An IFVG setup requires an aggressive V-shape reclaim through the fair value gap cluster. When price merely sweeps and consolidates without decisively closing through, avoid the trade — consolidation highs are likely just liquidity to be run before continuation lower.",
